[0m[49m[38;5;10m+     18[0m:[38;5;10m[49m - `comprehendmedical:InferRxNorm`
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+     19[0m:[38;5;10m[49m - `s3:GetObject`, `s3:PutObject`
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+     20[0m:[38;5;10m[49m - `dynamodb:PutItem`, `dynamodb:Query`
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+     21[0m:[38;5;10m[49m 
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+     22[0m:[38;5;10m[49m ---
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+     23[0m:[38;5;10m[49m 
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+     24[0m:[38;5;10m[49m ## Config and Constants
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+     25[0m:[38;5;10m[49m 
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+     26[0m:[38;5;10m[49m Before we get into the logic, here are the configuration values that drive the pipeline. These live at the top of your module because they're the first thing you'll want to tune when you deploy this against your own clinical notes.
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+     27[0m:[38;5;10m[49m 
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+     28[0m:[38;5;10m[49m ```python
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+     29[0m:[38;5;10m[49m import re
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+     30[0m:[38;5;10m[49m import json
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+     31[0m:[38;5;10m[49m import logging
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+     32[0m:[38;5;10m[49m import datetime
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+     33[0m:[38;5;10m[49m from datetime import timezone
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+     34[0m:[38;5;10m[49m from decimal import Decimal
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+     35[0m:[38;5;10m[49m 
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+     36[0m:[38;5;10m[49m import boto3
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+     37[0m:[38;5;10m[49m from botocore.config import Config
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+     38[0m:[38;5;10m[49m 
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+     39[0m:[38;5;10m[49m # Structured logging. In production, use JSON-formatted output for CloudWatch
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+     40[0m:[38;5;10m[49m # Logs Insights queries. Never log extracted medication text (it's PHI).
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+     41[0m:[38;5;10m[49m logger = logging.getLogger(__name__)
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+     42[0m:[38;5;10m[49m logger.setLevel(logging.INFO)
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+     43[0m:[38;5;10m[49m 
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+     44[0m:[38;5;10m[49m # Retry config: Comprehend Medical throttles under sustained load.
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+     45[0m:[38;5;10m[49m # Adaptive mode uses exponential backoff with jitter.
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+     46[0m:[38;5;10m[49m BOTO3_RETRY_CONFIG = Config(retries={"max_attempts": 3, "mode": "adaptive"})
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+     47[0m:[38;5;10m[49m 
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+     48[0m:[38;5;10m[49m # Clients
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+     49[0m:[38;5;10m[49m comprehend_medical = boto3.client("comprehendmedical", config=BOTO3_RETRY_CONFIG)
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+     50[0m:[38;5;10m[49m s3_client = boto3.client("s3", config=BOTO3_RETRY_CONFIG)
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+     51[0m:[38;5;10m[49m dynamodb = boto3.resource("dynamodb")
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+     52[0m:[38;5;10m[49m 
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+     53[0m:[38;5;10m[49m # Table and bucket names. Replace with your actual resource names.
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+     54[0m:[38;5;10m[49m MEDICATIONS_TABLE = "patient-medications"
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+     55[0m:[38;5;10m[49m RESULTS_BUCKET = "clinical-nlp-results"
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+     56[0m:[38;5;10m[49m 
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+     57[0m:[38;5;10m[49m # RxNorm normalization confidence threshold.
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+     58[0m:[38;5;10m[49m # Below this score, the mapping is flagged for pharmacist review rather than
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+     59[0m:[38;5;10m[49m # being accepted automatically. 0.70 is conservative; you might push this
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+     60[0m:[38;5;10m[49m # higher (0.80+) if you'd rather over-flag than under-flag.
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+     61[0m:[38;5;10m[49m RXNORM_CONFIDENCE_THRESHOLD = 0.70
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+     62[0m:[38;5;10m[49m 
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+     63[0m:[38;5;10m[49m # Section header patterns for clinical note parsing.
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+     64[0m:[38;5;10m[49m # These cover the most common structured note formats from major EHR vendors.
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+     65[0m:[38;5;10m[49m # You'll add to this list as you encounter new note templates.
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+     66[0m:[38;5;10m[49m MEDICATION_HEADERS = [
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+     67[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     "medications", "current medications", "home medications",
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+     68[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     "medications on admission", "discharge medications",
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+     69[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     "medication list", "meds", "active medications",
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+     70[0m:[38;5;10m[49m ]
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+     71[0m:[38;5;10m[49m ALLERGY_HEADERS = [
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+     72[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     "allergies", "drug allergies", "medication allergies",
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+     73[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     "allergy list", "adverse reactions",
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+     74[0m:[38;5;10m[49m ]
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+     75[0m:[38;5;10m[49m HISTORY_HEADERS = [
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+     76[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     "past medications", "prior medications", "medication history",
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+     77[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     "discontinued medications", "previous medications",
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+     78[0m:[38;5;10m[49m ]
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+     79[0m:[38;5;10m[49m ```
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+     80[0m:[38;5;10m[49m 
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+     81[0m:[38;5;10m[49m ---
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+     82[0m:[38;5;10m[49m 
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+     83[0m:[38;5;10m[49m ## Step 1: Detect Note Sections
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+     84[0m:[38;5;10m[49m 
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+     85[0m:[38;5;10m[49m *The pseudocode calls this `detect_sections(note_text)`. Clinical notes have structure (section headers like "MEDICATIONS:" or "ALLERGIES:") that tells us how to interpret medication mentions. A drug under "ALLERGIES" is an allergy, not an active med.*
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+     86[0m:[38;5;10m[49m 
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+     87[0m:[38;5;10m[49m ```python
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+     88[0m:[38;5;10m[49m def detect_sections(note_text: str) -> list[dict]:
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+     89[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     """
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+     90[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     Split a clinical note into sections by detecting header patterns.
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+     91[0m:[38;5;10m[49m 
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+     92[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     Clinical notes from EHR systems typically use patterns like:
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+     93[0m:[38;5;10m[49m       MEDICATIONS:
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+     94[0m:[38;5;10m[49m       **Current Medications**
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+     95[0m:[38;5;10m[49m       -- Allergies --
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+     96[0m:[38;5;10m[49m 
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+     97[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     We look for lines that match header-like patterns and use them as
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+     98[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     section boundaries. Each section gets a category (MEDICATION, ALLERGY,
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+     99[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     HISTORY, OTHER) that drives downstream context classification.
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    100[0m:[38;5;10m[49m 
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    101[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     Args:
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    102[0m:[38;5;10m[49m         note_text: Raw clinical note text, possibly with embedded section headers.
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    103[0m:[38;5;10m[49m 
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    104[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     Returns:
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    105[0m:[38;5;10m[49m         List of section dicts with keys: header, category, start, text.
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    106[0m:[38;5;10m[49m         If no headers are detected, the entire note is returned as a single
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    107[0m:[38;5;10m[49m         section with category "OTHER".
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    108[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     """
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    109[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     # Pattern: a line that looks like a header. Matches things like:
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    110[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     #   "MEDICATIONS:" or "Current Medications:" or "**Allergies**"
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    111[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     # Strips markdown bold markers and trailing colons/dashes for comparison.
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    112[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     header_pattern = re.compile(
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    113[0m:[38;5;10m[49m         r"^\s*[\*\-]*\s*([A-Za-z /]+?)\s*[\*\-]*\s*[:]*\s*$"
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    114[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     )
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    115[0m:[38;5;10m[49m 
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    116[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     sections = []
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    117[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     current_section = {
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    118[0m:[38;5;10m[49m         "header": "PREAMBLE",
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    119[0m:[38;5;10m[49m         "category": "OTHER",
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    120[0m:[38;5;10m[49m         "start": 0,
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    121[0m:[38;5;10m[49m         "text": "",
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    122[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     }
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    123[0m:[38;5;10m[49m 
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    124[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     for line in note_text.split("\n"):
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    125[0m:[38;5;10m[49m         match = header_pattern.match(line)
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    126[0m:[38;5;10m[49m         if match:
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    127[0m:[38;5;10m[49m             # Save the previous section if it has content.
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    128[0m:[38;5;10m[49m             if current_section["text"].strip():
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    129[0m:[38;5;10m[49m                 sections.append(current_section)
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    130[0m:[38;5;10m[49m 
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    131[0m:[38;5;10m[49m             header_text = match.group(1).strip().lower()
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    132[0m:[38;5;10m[49m 
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    133[0m:[38;5;10m[49m             # Classify this header.
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    134[0m:[38;5;10m[49m             if header_text in MEDICATION_HEADERS:
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    135[0m:[38;5;10m[49m                 category = "MEDICATION"
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    136[0m:[38;5;10m[49m             elif header_text in ALLERGY_HEADERS:
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    137[0m:[38;5;10m[49m                 category = "ALLERGY"
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    138[0m:[38;5;10m[49m             elif header_text in HISTORY_HEADERS:
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    139[0m:[38;5;10m[49m                 category = "HISTORY"
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    140[0m:[38;5;10m[49m             else:
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    141[0m:[38;5;10m[49m                 category = "OTHER"
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    142[0m:[38;5;10m[49m 
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    143[0m:[38;5;10m[49m             current_section = {
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    144[0m:[38;5;10m[49m                 "header": header_text,
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    145[0m:[38;5;10m[49m                 "category": category,
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    146[0m:[38;5;10m[49m                 "start": note_text.index(line),
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    147[0m:[38;5;10m[49m                 "text": "",
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    148[0m:[38;5;10m[49m             }
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    149[0m:[38;5;10m[49m         else:
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    150[0m:[38;5;10m[49m             current_section["text"] += line + "\n"
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    151[0m:[38;5;10m[49m 
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    152[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     # Don't forget the last section.
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    153[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     if current_section["text"].strip():
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    154[0m:[38;5;10m[49m         sections.append(current_section)
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    155[0m:[38;5;10m[49m 
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    156[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     return sections
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    157[0m:[38;5;10m[49m ```
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    158[0m:[38;5;10m[49m 
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    159[0m:[38;5;10m[49m ---
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    160[0m:[38;5;10m[49m 
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    161[0m:[38;5;10m[49m ## Step 2: Extract Medication Entities
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    162[0m:[38;5;10m[49m 
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    163[0m:[38;5;10m[49m *The pseudocode calls this `extract_medications(note_text)`. This is where Comprehend Medical does the heavy lifting. We send the note text and get back medication entities with their linked attributes (dose, route, frequency) and traits (negation, past history).*
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    164[0m:[38;5;10m[49m 
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    165[0m:[38;5;10m[49m ```python
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    166[0m:[38;5;10m[49m def extract_medications(note_text: str) -> list[dict]:
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    167[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     """
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    168[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     Call Amazon Comprehend Medical DetectEntitiesV2 to extract medication
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    169[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     entities from clinical text.
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    170[0m:[38;5;10m[49m 
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    171[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     DetectEntitiesV2 returns entities across multiple categories (MEDICATION,
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    172[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     MEDICAL_CONDITION, ANATOMY, etc.). We filter to MEDICATION entities and
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    173[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     collect their associated attributes (DOSAGE, FREQUENCY, ROUTE_OR_MODE,
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    174[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     FORM, DURATION, STRENGTH) and traits (NEGATION, PAST_HISTORY).
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    175[0m:[38;5;10m[49m 
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    176[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     The API handles attribute linking automatically: it knows that in
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    177[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     "lisinopril 20mg PO QD," the 20mg belongs to lisinopril.
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    178[0m:[38;5;10m[49m 
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    179[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     Args:
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    180[0m:[38;5;10m[49m         note_text: Clinical note text. Max 20,000 characters per call.
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    181[0m:[38;5;10m[49m                    Longer notes must be chunked (not shown here).
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    182[0m:[38;5;10m[49m 
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    183[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     Returns:
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    184[0m:[38;5;10m[49m         List of medication dicts with keys: text, begin, end, score,
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    185[0m:[38;5;10m[49m         attributes, traits.
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    186[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     """
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    187[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     response = comprehend_medical.detect_entities_v2(Text=note_text)
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    188[0m:[38;5;10m[49m 
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    189[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     medications = []
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    190[0m:[38;5;10m[49m 
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    191[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     for entity in response.get("Entities", []):
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    192[0m:[38;5;10m[49m         # Only process medication entities. Comprehend Medical also returns
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    193[0m:[38;5;10m[49m         # MEDICAL_CONDITION, TEST_TREATMENT_PROCEDURE, ANATOMY, etc.
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    194[0m:[38;5;10m[49m         if entity.get("Category") != "MEDICATION":
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    195[0m:[38;5;10m[49m             continue
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    196[0m:[38;5;10m[49m 
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    197[0m:[38;5;10m[49m         med = {
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    198[0m:[38;5;10m[49m             "text": entity["Text"],
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    199[0m:[38;5;10m[49m             "begin": entity["BeginOffset"],
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    200[0m:[38;5;10m[49m             "end": entity["EndOffset"],
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    201[0m:[38;5;10m[49m             "score": entity["Score"],
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    202[0m:[38;5;10m[49m             "attributes": {},
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    203[0m:[38;5;10m[49m             "traits": [],
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    204[0m:[38;5;10m[49m         }
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    205[0m:[38;5;10m[49m 
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    206[0m:[38;5;10m[49m         # Collect linked attributes: dose, frequency, route, form, etc.
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    207[0m:[38;5;10m[49m         # Comprehend Medical associates attributes with their parent entity,
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    208[0m:[38;5;10m[49m         # so "20mg" is already linked to "lisinopril" rather than floating free.
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    209[0m:[38;5;10m[49m         for attr in entity.get("Attributes", []):
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    210[0m:[38;5;10m[49m             med["attributes"][attr["Type"]] = {
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    211[0m:[38;5;10m[49m                 "text": attr["Text"],
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    212[0m:[38;5;10m[49m                 "score": attr["Score"],
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    213[0m:[38;5;10m[49m             }
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    214[0m:[38;5;10m[49m 
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    215[0m:[38;5;10m[49m         # Collect traits: NEGATION means the patient is NOT taking this.
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    216[0m:[38;5;10m[49m         # PAST_HISTORY means it's a historical medication, not current.
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    217[0m:[38;5;10m[49m         for trait in entity.get("Traits", []):
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    218[0m:[38;5;10m[49m             med["traits"].append(trait["Name"])
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    219[0m:[38;5;10m[49m 
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    220[0m:[38;5;10m[49m         medications.append(med)
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    221[0m:[38;5;10m[49m 
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    222[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     return medications
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    223[0m:[38;5;10m[49m ```
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    224[0m:[38;5;10m[49m 
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    225[0m:[38;5;10m[49m ---
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    226[0m:[38;5;10m[49m 
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    227[0m:[38;5;10m[49m ## Step 3: Normalize to RxNorm
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    228[0m:[38;5;10m[49m 
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    229[0m:[38;5;10m[49m *The pseudocode calls this `normalize_to_rxnorm(medication_text)`. This maps raw extracted text like "lisinopril 20mg" to a standard RxCUI (314077), enabling interoperability with pharmacy systems, formularies, and drug interaction databases.*
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    230[0m:[38;5;10m[49m 
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    231[0m:[38;5;10m[49m ```python
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    232[0m:[38;5;10m[49m def normalize_to_rxnorm(medication_text: str) -> dict:
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    233[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     """
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    234[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     Map extracted medication text to an RxNorm concept using InferRxNorm.
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    235[0m:[38;5;10m[49m 
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    236[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     InferRxNorm takes free-text medication mentions and returns ranked
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    237[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     candidate RxNorm concepts with confidence scores. This is what turns
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    238[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     "Zestril 20mg" and "lisinopril 20 mg tab" into the same RxCUI.
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    239[0m:[38;5;10m[49m 
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    240[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     The API handles brand-to-generic resolution, common abbreviations,
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    241[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     and dose-form disambiguation. For ambiguous cases (combination drugs,
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    242[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     non-standard abbreviations), it returns multiple candidates.
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    243[0m:[38;5;10m[49m 
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    244[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     Args:
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    245[0m:[38;5;10m[49m         medication_text: Raw medication text from the extraction step.
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    246[0m:[38;5;10m[49m                          e.g., "lisinopril 20mg" or "Lipitor 40"
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    247[0m:[38;5;10m[49m 
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    248[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     Returns:
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    249[0m:[38;5;10m[49m         Dict with keys: rxcui, description, score, status.
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    250[0m:[38;5;10m[49m         status is one of: MATCHED, NEEDS_REVIEW, UNMATCHED.
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    251[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     """
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    252[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     response = comprehend_medical.infer_rx_norm(Text=medication_text)
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    253[0m:[38;5;10m[49m 
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    254[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     # InferRxNorm returns entities, each with a list of RxNormConcepts.
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    255[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     # We flatten and sort by score to find the best match.
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    256[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     candidates = []
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    257[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     for entity in response.get("Entities", []):
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    258[0m:[38;5;10m[49m         for concept in entity.get("RxNormConcepts", []):
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    259[0m:[38;5;10m[49m             candidates.append({
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    260[0m:[38;5;10m[49m                 "rxcui": concept["RxCUI"],
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    261[0m:[38;5;10m[49m                 "description": concept["Description"],
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    262[0m:[38;5;10m[49m                 "score": concept["Score"],
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    263[0m:[38;5;10m[49m             })
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    264[0m:[38;5;10m[49m 
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    265[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     # Sort by confidence, highest first.
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    266[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     candidates.sort(key=lambda c: c["score"], reverse=True)
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    267[0m:[38;5;10m[49m 
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    268[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     if candidates and candidates[0]["score"] >= RXNORM_CONFIDENCE_THRESHOLD:
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    269[0m:[38;5;10m[49m         return {
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    270[0m:[38;5;10m[49m             "rxcui": candidates[0]["rxcui"],
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    271[0m:[38;5;10m[49m             "description": candidates[0]["description"],
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    272[0m:[38;5;10m[49m             "score": candidates[0]["score"],
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    273[0m:[38;5;10m[49m             "status": "MATCHED",
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    274[0m:[38;5;10m[49m         }
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    275[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     elif candidates:
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    276[0m:[38;5;10m[49m         # Best guess exists but confidence is too low. Flag for pharmacist review.
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    277[0m:[38;5;10m[49m         return {
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    278[0m:[38;5;10m[49m             "rxcui": candidates[0]["rxcui"],
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    279[0m:[38;5;10m[49m             "description": candidates[0]["description"],
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    280[0m:[38;5;10m[49m             "score": candidates[0]["score"],
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    281[0m:[38;5;10m[49m             "status": "NEEDS_REVIEW",
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    282[0m:[38;5;10m[49m         }
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    283[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     else:
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    284[0m:[38;5;10m[49m         # No candidates at all. Could be a misspelling, unusual abbreviation,
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    285[0m:[38;5;10m[49m         # or a non-medication entity that leaked through.
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    286[0m:[38;5;10m[49m         return {
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    287[0m:[38;5;10m[49m             "rxcui": None,
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    288[0m:[38;5;10m[49m             "description": None,
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    289[0m:[38;5;10m[49m             "score": 0.0,
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    290[0m:[38;5;10m[49m             "status": "UNMATCHED",
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    291[0m:[38;5;10m[49m         }
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    292[0m:[38;5;10m[49m ```
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    293[0m:[38;5;10m[49m 
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    294[0m:[38;5;10m[49m ---
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    295[0m:[38;5;10m[49m 
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    296[0m:[38;5;10m[49m ## Step 4: Classify Context and Assertion Status
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    297[0m:[38;5;10m[49m 
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    298[0m:[38;5;10m[49m *The pseudocode calls this `classify_medication_context(med, section_category)`. Not every medication mention belongs on the active list. This step combines NER traits and section context to determine if a medication is active, historical, negated, or an allergy.*
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    299[0m:[38;5;10m[49m 
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    300[0m:[38;5;10m[49m ```python
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    301[0m:[38;5;10m[49m def classify_medication_context(med: dict, section_category: str) -> str:
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    302[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     """
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    303[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     Determine the assertion status of an extracted medication mention.
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    304[0m:[38;5;10m[49m 
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    305[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     Uses two signals:
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    306[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     1. NER traits from Comprehend Medical (NEGATION, PAST_HISTORY)
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    307[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     2. Which note section the medication was found in
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    308[0m:[38;5;10m[49m 
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    309[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     This is what prevents your medication list from including drugs the patient
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    310[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     explicitly said they don't take, or allergies that shouldn't be on the
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    311[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     active med list.
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    312[0m:[38;5;10m[49m 
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    313[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     Args:
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    314[0m:[38;5;10m[49m         med: A medication dict from extract_medications() with a "traits" list.
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    315[0m:[38;5;10m[49m         section_category: The category of the note section where this med was
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    316[0m:[38;5;10m[49m                           found (MEDICATION, ALLERGY, HISTORY, OTHER).
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    317[0m:[38;5;10m[49m 
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    318[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     Returns:
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    319[0m:[38;5;10m[49m         One of: "ACTIVE", "NEGATED", "HISTORICAL", "ALLERGY".
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    320[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     """
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    321[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     # Negation trait overrides everything. "Denies taking metformin" or
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    322[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     # "not currently on lisinopril" should never appear as active meds.
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    323[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     if "NEGATION" in med["traits"]:
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    324[0m:[38;5;10m[49m         return "NEGATED"
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    325[0m:[38;5;10m[49m 
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    326[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     # Past history trait: "was on," "previously took," "prior to admission."
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    327[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     if "PAST_HISTORY" in med["traits"]:
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    328[0m:[38;5;10m[49m         return "HISTORICAL"
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    329[0m:[38;5;10m[49m 
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    330[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     # Section-based classification for cases where traits alone are insufficient.
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    331[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     if section_category == "ALLERGY":
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    332[0m:[38;5;10m[49m         return "ALLERGY"
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    333[0m:[38;5;10m[49m 
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    334[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     if section_category == "HISTORY":
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    335[0m:[38;5;10m[49m         return "HISTORICAL"
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    336[0m:[38;5;10m[49m 
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    337[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     # Default: medication found in active meds section or in narrative
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    338[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     # without negation or historical markers. Conservative choice: treat
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    339[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     # as active unless proven otherwise.
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    340[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     return "ACTIVE"
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    341[0m:[38;5;10m[49m ```
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    342[0m:[38;5;10m[49m 
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    343[0m:[38;5;10m[49m ---
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    344[0m:[38;5;10m[49m 
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    345[0m:[38;5;10m[49m ## Step 5: Assemble and Store Structured Medication Records
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    346[0m:[38;5;10m[49m 
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    347[0m:[38;5;10m[49m *The pseudocode calls this `store_medication_extraction(patient_id, note_id, medications, sections)`. This combines everything into a final structured record and writes it to DynamoDB and S3.*
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    348[0m:[38;5;10m[49m 
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    349[0m:[38;5;10m[49m ```python
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    350[0m:[38;5;10m[49m def find_section_for_offset(sections: list[dict], offset: int) -> dict:
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    351[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     """
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    352[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     Determine which note section contains a given character offset.
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    353[0m:[38;5;10m[49m 
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    354[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     We walk the sections in reverse order (largest start offset first) and
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    355[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     return the first section whose start position is at or before the offset.
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    356[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     """
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    357[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     # Sort sections by start position descending for lookup.
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    358[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     sorted_sections = sorted(sections, key=lambda s: s["start"], reverse=True)
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    359[0m:[38;5;10m[49m 
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    360[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     for section in sorted_sections:
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    361[0m:[38;5;10m[49m         if offset >= section["start"]:
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    362[0m:[38;5;10m[49m             return section
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    363[0m:[38;5;10m[49m 
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    364[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     # Fallback: if no section matched, return a generic one.
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    365[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     return {"header": "unknown", "category": "OTHER"}
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    366[0m:[38;5;10m[49m 
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    367[0m:[38;5;10m[49m 
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    368[0m:[38;5;10m[49m def store_medication_extraction(
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    369[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     patient_id: str,
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    370[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     note_id: str,
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    371[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     medications: list[dict],
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    372[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     sections: list[dict],
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    373[0m:[38;5;10m[49m ) -> list[dict]:
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    374[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     """
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    375[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     For each extracted medication: normalize to RxNorm, classify context,
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    376[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     build a structured record, and write to DynamoDB + S3.
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    377[0m:[38;5;10m[49m 
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    378[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     This is the final assembly step. Downstream systems (medication
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    379[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     reconciliation, drug interaction checking, clinical decision support)
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    380[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     consume these structured records rather than re-parsing notes.
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    381[0m:[38;5;10m[49m 
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    382[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     Args:
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    383[0m:[38;5;10m[49m         patient_id: Unique patient identifier.
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    384[0m:[38;5;10m[49m         note_id: Unique identifier for the source clinical note.
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    385[0m:[38;5;10m[49m         medications: List of medication dicts from extract_medications().
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    386[0m:[38;5;10m[49m         sections: List of section dicts from detect_sections().
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    387[0m:[38;5;10m[49m 
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    388[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     Returns:
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    389[0m:[38;5;10m[49m         List of structured medication records that were stored.
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    390[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     """
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    391[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     table = dynamodb.Table(MEDICATIONS_TABLE)
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    392[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     extraction_ts = datetime.datetime.now(timezone.utc).isoformat()
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    393[0m:[38;5;10m[49m 
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    394[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     structured_meds = []
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    395[0m:[38;5;10m[49m 
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    396[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     for med in medications:
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    397[0m:[38;5;10m[49m         # Which section was this medication found in?
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    398[0m:[38;5;10m[49m         section = find_section_for_offset(sections, med["begin"])
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    399[0m:[38;5;10m[49m 
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    400[0m:[38;5;10m[49m         # Classify assertion status (active, negated, historical, allergy).
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    401[0m:[38;5;10m[49m         assertion = classify_medication_context(med, section["category"])
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    402[0m:[38;5;10m[49m 
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    403[0m:[38;5;10m[49m         # Normalize to RxNorm.
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    404[0m:[38;5;10m[49m         rxnorm = normalize_to_rxnorm(med["text"])
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    405[0m:[38;5;10m[49m 
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    406[0m:[38;5;10m[49m         # Build the structured record.
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    407[0m:[38;5;10m[49m         record = {
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    408[0m:[38;5;10m[49m             "patient_id": patient_id,
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    409[0m:[38;5;10m[49m             "sort_key": f"{extraction_ts}#{note_id}#{med['begin']}",
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    410[0m:[38;5;10m[49m             "note_id": note_id,
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    411[0m:[38;5;10m[49m             "medication_text": med["text"],
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    412[0m:[38;5;10m[49m             "rxcui": rxnorm["rxcui"],
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    413[0m:[38;5;10m[49m             "rxnorm_description": rxnorm["description"],
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    414[0m:[38;5;10m[49m             # DynamoDB requires Decimal for numbers, not float.
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    415[0m:[38;5;10m[49m             # Wrapping via str() avoids floating-point representation issues.
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    416[0m:[38;5;10m[49m             "rxnorm_score": Decimal(str(round(rxnorm["score"], 4))),
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    417[0m:[38;5;10m[49m             "rxnorm_status": rxnorm["status"],
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    418[0m:[38;5;10m[49m             "dosage": med["attributes"].get("DOSAGE", {}).get("text"),
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    419[0m:[38;5;10m[49m             "frequency": med["attributes"].get("FREQUENCY", {}).get("text"),
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    420[0m:[38;5;10m[49m             "route": med["attributes"].get("ROUTE_OR_MODE", {}).get("text"),
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    421[0m:[38;5;10m[49m             "form": med["attributes"].get("FORM", {}).get("text"),
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    422[0m:[38;5;10m[49m             "duration": med["attributes"].get("DURATION", {}).get("text"),
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    423[0m:[38;5;10m[49m             "strength": med["attributes"].get("STRENGTH", {}).get("text"),
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    424[0m:[38;5;10m[49m             "assertion": assertion,
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    425[0m:[38;5;10m[49m             "confidence": Decimal(str(round(med["score"], 4))),
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    426[0m:[38;5;10m[49m             "source_section": section["header"],
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    427[0m:[38;5;10m[49m             "extraction_ts": extraction_ts,
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    428[0m:[38;5;10m[49m         }
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    429[0m:[38;5;10m[49m 
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    430[0m:[38;5;10m[49m         structured_meds.append(record)
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    431[0m:[38;5;10m[49m 
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    432[0m:[38;5;10m[49m         # Write to DynamoDB. Partition key: patient_id, sort key: composite.
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    433[0m:[38;5;10m[49m         table.put_item(Item=record)
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    434[0m:[38;5;10m[49m 
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    435[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     # Write full extraction to S3 for audit trail and reprocessing.
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    436[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     s3_key = f"results/{patient_id}/{note_id}/medications.json"
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    437[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     s3_client.put_object(
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    438[0m:[38;5;10m[49m         Bucket=RESULTS_BUCKET,
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    439[0m:[38;5;10m[49m         Key=s3_key,
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    440[0m:[38;5;10m[49m         Body=json.dumps(structured_meds, default=str),
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    441[0m:[38;5;10m[49m         ContentType="application/json",
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    442[0m:[38;5;10m[49m         ServerSideEncryption="aws:kms",
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    443[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     )
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    444[0m:[38;5;10m[49m 
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    445[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     return structured_meds
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    446[0m:[38;5;10m[49m ```
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    447[0m:[38;5;10m[49m 
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    448[0m:[38;5;10m[49m ---
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    449[0m:[38;5;10m[49m 
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    450[0m:[38;5;10m[49m ## Putting It All Together
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    451[0m:[38;5;10m[49m 
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    452[0m:[38;5;10m[49m Here's the full pipeline assembled into a single function. This is what your Lambda handler would call when a new clinical note arrives.
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    453[0m:[38;5;10m[49m 
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    454[0m:[38;5;10m[49m ```python
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    455[0m:[38;5;10m[49m # Synthetic clinical note for demonstration.
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    456[0m:[38;5;10m[49m # This covers the common scenarios: active meds, allergies, historical meds,
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    457[0m:[38;5;10m[49m # and a negated medication. In production, this text comes from S3 or an
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    458[0m:[38;5;10m[49m # HL7 message feed.
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    459[0m:[38;5;10m[49m SAMPLE_NOTE = """
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    460[0m:[38;5;10m[49m Patient: Jane Doe
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    461[0m:[38;5;10m[49m Date: 2026-03-01
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    462[0m:[38;5;10m[49m Provider: Dr. Smith
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    463[0m:[38;5;10m[49m 
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    464[0m:[38;5;10m[49m Current Medications:
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    465[0m:[38;5;10m[49m Lisinopril 20mg oral daily
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    466[0m:[38;5;10m[49m Metformin 500mg oral twice daily
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    467[0m:[38;5;10m[49m Atorvastatin 40mg oral at bedtime
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    468[0m:[38;5;10m[49m 
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    469[0m:[38;5;10m[49m Allergies:
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    470[0m:[38;5;10m[49m Penicillin (rash)
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    471[0m:[38;5;10m[49m Sulfa drugs (anaphylaxis)
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    472[0m:[38;5;10m[49m 
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    473[0m:[38;5;10m[49m Past Medications:
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    474[0m:[38;5;10m[49m Amlodipine 5mg - discontinued 2025-06 due to edema
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    475[0m:[38;5;10m[49m 
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    476[0m:[38;5;10m[49m Assessment:
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    477[0m:[38;5;10m[49m Patient is well-controlled on current regimen. She is not taking aspirin
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    478[0m:[38;5;10m[49m despite prior recommendation. Will continue current medications. Consider
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    479[0m:[38;5;10m[49m adding low-dose aspirin at next visit.
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    480[0m:[38;5;10m[49m """
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    481[0m:[38;5;10m[49m 
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    482[0m:[38;5;10m[49m 
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    483[0m:[38;5;10m[49m def process_clinical_note(patient_id: str, note_id: str, note_text: str) -> list[dict]:
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    484[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     """
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    485[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     Run the full medication extraction and normalization pipeline for one note.
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    486[0m:[38;5;10m[49m 
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    487[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     Steps:
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    488[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     1. Detect note sections (medications, allergies, history, etc.)
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    489[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     2. Extract medication entities with attributes and traits
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    490[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     3. For each medication: normalize to RxNorm, classify context, store
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    491[0m:[38;5;10m[49m 
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    492[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     Args:
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    493[0m:[38;5;10m[49m         patient_id: Unique patient identifier.
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    494[0m:[38;5;10m[49m         note_id: Unique identifier for this clinical note.
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    495[0m:[38;5;10m[49m         note_text: Raw text of the clinical note.
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    496[0m:[38;5;10m[49m 
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    497[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     Returns:
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    498[0m:[38;5;10m[49m         List of structured medication records.
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    499[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     """
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    500[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     # Step 1: Section detection.
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    501[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     logger.info("Step 1: Detecting note sections")
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    502[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     sections = detect_sections(note_text)
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    503[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     logger.info("  Found %d sections", len(sections))
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    504[0m:[38;5;10m[49m 
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    505[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     # Step 2: NER extraction.
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    506[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     logger.info("Step 2: Extracting medication entities")
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    507[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     medications = extract_medications(note_text)
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    508[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     logger.info("  Found %d medication mentions", len(medications))
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    509[0m:[38;5;10m[49m 
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    510[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     # Steps 3-5: Normalize, classify, and store each medication.
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    511[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     logger.info("Steps 3-5: Normalizing, classifying, and storing")
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    512[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     results = store_medication_extraction(patient_id, note_id, medications, sections)
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    513[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     logger.info("  Stored %d structured medication records", len(results))
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    514[0m:[38;5;10m[49m 
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    515[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     return results
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    516[0m:[38;5;10m[49m 
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    517[0m:[38;5;10m[49m 
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    518[0m:[38;5;10m[49m if __name__ == "__main__":
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    519[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     results = process_clinical_note(
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    520[0m:[38;5;10m[49m         patient_id="PAT-2026-00482",
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    521[0m:[38;5;10m[49m         note_id="NOTE-20260301-1422",
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    522[0m:[38;5;10m[49m         note_text=SAMPLE_NOTE,
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    523[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     )
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    524[0m:[38;5;10m[49m 
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    525[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     # Print results for inspection. In production, these would flow to
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    526[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     # medication reconciliation workflows or clinical decision support.
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    527[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     for med in results:
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    528[0m:[38;5;10m[49m         print(f"  {med['medication_text']:25s} -> {med['rxnorm_description'] or 'UNMATCHED':40s} "
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    529[0m:[38;5;10m[49m               f"[{med['assertion']:10s}] (RxNorm score: {med['rxnorm_score']})")
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    530[0m:[38;5;10m[49m ```
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    531[0m:[38;5;10m[49m 
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    532[0m:[38;5;10m[49m ---
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    533[0m:[38;5;10m[49m 
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    534[0m:[38;5;10m[49m ## The Gap Between This and Production
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    535[0m:[38;5;10m[49m 
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    536[0m:[38;5;10m[49m This example works. Point it at a real clinical note and Comprehend Medical will return structured medication extractions with RxNorm codes. But there's a meaningful distance between "works in a script" and "runs in a health system processing thousands of notes daily." Here's where that gap lives:
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    537[0m:[38;5;10m[49m 
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    538[0m:[38;5;10m[49m **Error handling.** Right now, if Comprehend Medical returns an error (throttling, service unavailability, malformed input), the script crashes. A production system wraps every API call in try/except blocks with specific handling for `ThrottlingException`, `TextSizeLimitExceededException`, and `InternalServerException`. You want graceful degradation and dead-letter queues, not silent note loss.
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    539[0m:[38;5;10m[49m 
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    540[0m:[38;5;10m[49m **Text size limits.** Comprehend Medical's DetectEntitiesV2 accepts a maximum of 20,000 UTF-8 characters per call. Clinical notes (especially discharge summaries) can exceed this. A production system chunks long notes at section boundaries, processes each chunk, and merges results with offset correction. The chunking logic isn't trivial because you can't split mid-sentence without risking attribute-linking errors.
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    541[0m:[38;5;10m[49m 
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    542[0m:[38;5;10m[49m **Retries and backoff.** The adaptive retry config handles basic throttling, but for batch processing (running through thousands of historical notes), you'll want a rate-limiting layer. Comprehend Medical has per-account transactions-per-second limits. Step Functions with a Map state and a concurrency limit is the standard pattern for controlled batch throughput.
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    543[0m:[38;5;10m[49m 
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    544[0m:[38;5;10m[49m **Input validation.** This code trusts that note_text is a valid UTF-8 string within size limits. A production system validates encoding, rejects binary content, strips null bytes, and checks character count before calling the API. Clinical text from HL7 feeds sometimes arrives with encoding issues or embedded control characters.
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    545[0m:[38;5;10m[49m 
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    546[0m:[38;5;10m[49m **Logging and observability.** The `logger.info()` calls here are placeholders. A real system emits structured metrics: medications extracted per note, RxNorm match rate, assertion distribution, processing latency. CloudWatch custom metrics or embedded metric format lets you build dashboards and alarms. Never log the actual medication text (it's PHI); log counts, scores, and statuses.
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    547[0m:[38;5;10m[49m 
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    548[0m:[38;5;10m[49m **IAM least-privilege.** The IAM role for this Lambda needs exactly: `comprehendmedical:DetectEntitiesV2` and `comprehendmedical:InferRxNorm` on all resources, `s3:GetObject` and `s3:PutObject` scoped to specific buckets, `dynamodb:PutItem` scoped to the specific table. No wildcards. No `AdministratorAccess`.
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    549[0m:[38;5;10m[49m 
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    550[0m:[38;5;10m[49m **VPC configuration.** Clinical notes contain PHI. In production, the Lambda runs in a VPC with private subnets and VPC endpoints for Comprehend Medical, S3, DynamoDB, and CloudWatch Logs. API traffic stays on the AWS backbone and never traverses the public internet.
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    551[0m:[38;5;10m[49m 
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    552[0m:[38;5;10m[49m **Encryption key management.** This example uses default encryption (`aws:kms`). Production uses customer-managed KMS keys (CMKs) with rotation enabled and CloudTrail logging of all key usage. S3, DynamoDB, and CloudWatch Logs each get their own CMK with appropriately scoped key policies.
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    553[0m:[38;5;10m[49m 
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    554[0m:[38;5;10m[49m **DynamoDB data types.** The code already wraps numeric values in `Decimal()` (see Step 5), but be aware that any new numeric field you add must also use `Decimal`. The boto3 DynamoDB resource layer raises a `TypeError` on raw Python floats in `put_item` calls. Converting via `str()` first avoids floating-point representation issues (e.g., `Decimal(0.1)` produces `0.100000000000000005551115...` while `Decimal("0.1")` produces `0.1`).
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    555[0m:[38;5;10m[49m 
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    556[0m:[38;5;10m[49m **RxNorm version management.** RxNorm is updated monthly by the NLM. AWS updates the version used by InferRxNorm on their own schedule. This means RxCUI mappings can shift between runs. A production system records the API version or response metadata with each extraction so you can trace which RxNorm version produced a given mapping.
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    557[0m:[38;5;10m[49m 
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    558[0m:[38;5;10m[49m **Combination drug handling.** "HCTZ/lisinopril 12.5/20" is a single mention of a combination drug. InferRxNorm handles many of these, but some require splitting into components and normalizing each ingredient separately. A production system has fallback logic for combination drugs that don't resolve cleanly.
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    559[0m:[38;5;10m[49m 
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    560[0m:[38;5;10m[49m **Pharmacist review workflow.** Medications with `NEEDS_REVIEW` or `UNMATCHED` status need a human review queue. This example stores the flag but doesn't implement the review UI or approval workflow. In practice, you'd send these to a pharmacist review queue (could be a FHIR Task, a work item in the EHR, or a custom review application) and update the record once adjudicated.
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    561[0m:[38;5;10m[49m 
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    562[0m:[38;5;10m[49m **Testing.** There are no tests here. A production pipeline has unit tests for `detect_sections` (with synthetic notes covering common EHR templates), integration tests against Comprehend Medical with known test notes, and a golden dataset of annotated medication mentions for measuring extraction accuracy over time. Never use real patient notes in your test fixtures.
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    563[0m:[38;5;10m[49m 
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    564[0m:[38;5;10m[49m ---
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    565[0m:[38;5;10m[49m 
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    566[0m:[38;5;10m[49m *Part of the Healthcare AI/ML Cookbook. See [Recipe 8.4](chapter08.04-medication-extraction-normalization) for the full architectural walkthrough, pseudocode, and honest take on where medication extraction gets hard.*
